<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910618-0032</DOCNO><DOCID>910618-0032.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Russ Togs Inc.:   First-Quarter Loss Widened   69% to Total $2.5 Million</HL><DATE>06/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12</SO><CO>   RTS</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)TEXTILES AND APPAREL (TEX)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Russ Togs Inc. reported that its first-quarter losswidened 69% to $2.5 million because of continued weakness inthe retail apparel environment and charges related tochanging its product mix.   The loss for the quarter ended May 4, which equals 35cents a share, compares with a loss of $1.5 million, or 21cents a share, the year before. The latest quarter's resultsinclude $232,000 in restructuring charges and $845,000 in netinterest expenses. A Russ Togs spokesman said the New Yorkcompany has been reducing unbranded, lower-margin merchandisein its product mix.</LP><TEXT>   Kenneth Sitomer, president and chief executive officer,said the restructuring is beginning to yield results, citinga 13% jump in sales to $56.6 million from $50 million in the1990 quarter, which ended May 5.</TEXT></DOC>